    <string-array name="questions">
        <item>How to begin?</item>
        <item>How to change the number of categories?</item>
        <item>How to rename categories?</item>
        <item>How to change the currency designation?</item>
        <item>How to change the amount of an account?</item>
        <item>How to transfer money between accounts?</item>
        <item>How to add a transaction?</item>
        <item>How to edit a transaction?</item>
        <item>How to delete a transaction?</item>
    </string-array>

    <string-array name="answers">
        <item>
            First of all, decide the number of categories of incomes and expenses.
            Next, rename the categories according to your preferences.
            Then enter the values of the amounts of your accounts in accordance with the real
            state of affairs. Select your preferred currency. Then you can proceed
            to the introduction of expenses, incomes for past and current periods.
        </item>
        <item>
            Go to the “Settings” menu item. In the “Number of categories” section,
            select the required number of categories.
        </item>
        <item>
            Go to the “Settings” menu item. In the “Category name” section, rename the categories.
        </item>
        <item>
            Go to the “Settings” menu item. In the “Currency” section, select the currency designation.
        </item>
        <item>
            Account status is displayed on the first screen “Dashboard”. Click and
            hold down the card with the selected account. The dialog box for changing
            the amount appears. Enter the amount and click "OK".
        </item>
        <item>
            Account status is displayed on the first screen “Dashboard”. Click and
            hold down the card with the selected account. The dialog box for changing
            the amount appears. Check the "Transfer" checkbox and select the account
            from which the specified amount will be written off.
        </item>
        <item>
            You can add a transaction from any application screen by clicking
            “+” button. Next, a dialog box appears,
            in which you can enter the necessary information about the transaction.
        </item>
        <item>
            You can edit the transaction on the detailed screen
            display the corresponding category. Swipe on the transaction to the right, start editing mode.
        </item>

        <item>
            You can delete a transaction on the detailed screen
            display the corresponding category. Swipe on the transaction to the left, start the delete mode.
        </item>
    </string-array>

    <string-array name="questions_budget">
        <item>About the budget planner</item>
        <item>How to plan a budget?</item>
        <item>How to add a budget item?</item>
        <item>How to edit a budget item?</item>
        <item>how to delete a budget item?</item>
    </string-array>


    <string-array name="answers_budget">
       <item>
           The budget planner allows you to plan the annual and monthly budgets.
           The annual budget consists of 12 monthly budgets, the name of each of 12 coincides with
           the name of the appropriate calendar month. Number and category name
           in each budget is equal to the general settings of the application. From the main application screen
           you can track how much is left to spend - earn this month to fulfill the budget.
        </item>
        <item>
            You can start planning the budget with periodically recurring budget items.
            For example, if you get approximately the same salary each month and advance payment out of their first
            by tapping the "+" button. Please note, in the mode of entering a budget item, you can select the "repeat every month" mode.
            And the budget item will be duplicated every month from January. Then you can more details
            to plan the budget of each month by adding the budget items, as well as editing previously added.
            It is necessary to ensure that the income/cost ratio is positive. It is allowed to have a negative income/cost ratio
            in some months, but the annual result should be positive. The optimum value is about + 20%.
        </item>
        <item>
            You can add a budget item from any budget planner screen by tapping "+" button.
            Next, a dialog box appears in which you can enter necessary information.
        </item>
        <item>
            You can edit the budget item on the detailed screen. Swipe
            on the budget item to the right, the editing mode will start.
        </item>
        <item>
            You can delete a budget item from the detailed screen.
            Swipe on the budget item to the left, the delete mode will start.
        </item>
    </string-array>


